  "text": "Currently, all scientific theories on BD indicate its autoimmune etiology. However, the attempts at determining whether tissue antigens play a role in channeling the immune response have been unsuccessful so far. Elevated peripheral levels of γδ T cells (γδ + T cells) in patients with BD in response to exposure to mycobacterial heat shock proteins (HSPs) compared with those found in healthy subjects imply an influence on the disease pathogenesis [CITATION_1] . HSP-65, found in high concentrations in oral ulcers and active skin lesions in patients with BD, was also demonstrated to stimulate production of antibodies that exhibit cross-reactivity with streptococcal species present in the mouth [CITATION_2] .",
